### ANNOTATION ###

Structural and Functional Genome Annotation
1.	Repeat Identification and Masking

buildDatabase -name LB0111_DB LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa
repeatModeler -database LB0111_DB -threads 80
repeatMasker -pa 80 -lib consensi.fa.classified -xsmall -gff LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa

2.	 Transcriptomic Evidence
Public paired-end RNA-seq datasets (ERR12356292 and SRR10852993) were aligned against the masked genome using HISAT2 v2.2.1.
hisat2-build LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa.masked LB0111_masked
hisat2 -p 80 -x LB0111_masked -1 ERR12356292_1.fastq.gz -2 ERR12356292_2.fastq.gz | samtools sort -o ERR12356292.sorted.bam

samtools index ERR12356292.sorted.bam
3.	 Protein Evidence
Protein sequences from Phalacrocorax carbo (bPhaCar2.1) and Gulosus aristotelis (bGulAri2.1) were filtered to remove proteins shorter than 50 amino acids and clustered with CD-HIT v4.8.1 at 99% identity to obtain a non-redundant protein dataset.
cd-hit -i proteins.fa -o proteins_nr.fa -c 0.99 -T 80 -M 0
4.	Gene Prediction
braker.pl --genome=LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa.masked --bam=ERR12356292.sorted.bam,SRR10852993.sorted.bam --prot_seq=proteins_nr.fa --threads=80 –etpmode

5.	 Annotation Assessment
busco -i proteins.fa -l aves_odb10 -m proteins -c 80
busco -i proteins.fa -l eukaryota_odb10 -m proteins -c 80

6.	 Functional Annotation
emapper.py -i proteins.fa -o eggnog -m diamond --cpu 80
interproscan.sh -i proteins.fa -f tsv,gff3 -cpu 80

